(688, 'Student Volunteers', 'student-volunteers', '', '<div class="overview">\n<table >\n\n<tr class="committee">\n<th colspan="3">Student Volunteers</th>\n</tr>\n\n<tr >\n<td ><a href="mailto:student_volunteers@splashcon.org">Gregor Richards</a>*</td>\n<td >Purdue U</td>\n<td >USA</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr >\n<td ><a href="mailto:student_volunteers@splashcon.org">Jonathan Bell</a>*</td>\n<td >Columbia U</td>\n<td >USA</td>\n</tr>\n\n</table>\n* chair</div>\n', '', 1, 0, 0, 196, '2013-05-03 02:03:26', 0, '', '2013-05-03 02:03:26', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2013-05-03 02:03:26', '2033-05-03 02:03:26', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=\n', 1, 0, 8, '', '', 0, 1701, ''),
(689, 'Student Volunteers', 'student-volunteers', '', '<p>The SPLASH Student Volunteer program provides an opportunity for students from around the world to associate with some of the leading personalities in industry and research in the following areas: programming languages, object-oriented technology and software development. Student volunteers contribute to the smooth running of the conference by performing tasks such as: assisting with registration, providing information about the conference to attendees, assisting session organizers and monitoring sessions.</p>', '<div class="">\n<table class="view cfp-submission-summary" cellspacing="0">\n\n<tr >\n<th colspan="2">Submission Summary</th>\n</tr>\n\n<tr >\n<td >Due on:</td>\n<td >August 01, 2013</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr >\n<td >Notifications:</td>\n<td >August 08, 2013</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr >\n<td >Format:</td>\n<td ><a href="http://goo.gl/u9n5f" target="_blank">online form</a></td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr >\n<td >Submit to:</td>\n<td ><a href="http://goo.gl/u9n5f" target="_blank">http://goo.gl/u9n5f</a></td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr >\n<td >Contact:</td>\n<td ><a href="mailto:student_volunteers@splashcon.org">Gregor Richards and Jonathan Bell</a> (chair)</td>\n</tr>\n\n</table>\n<p>The ACM International Conference on Systems, Programming, Languages and Applications: Software for Humanity (SPLASH) is sponsored by ACM SIGPLAN.</p>\n\n<p>SPLASH is the home of OOPSLA Research Papers, Onward!, and the Dynamic Languages Symposium, among other events.</p><h3>Selection Process</h3>\n\n<p>All student volunteers are required to submit the online application by the deadline using the linked spreadsheet. Remember to also have your advisor submit a recommendation letter (applications will not be considered without recommendations). All student volunteers are expected to be available from October 27–31 (a few volunteers will be required to be available from October 26-31).</p>\n\n<h3>Student Volunteer Benefits</h3>\n\n<p>In exchange for performing their volunteer duties, student volunteers receive:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Complimentary student conference registration</li>\n<li>Custom SPLASH garment</li>\n<li>Admission to all conference events (based on available space)</li>\n<li>Admission to all conference receptions</li>\n<li>And more! (coming soon)</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=""><h3>For More Information</h3>\n<p>For additional information, clarification, or answers to questions please contact the Student Volunteers Chair, Gregor Richards and Jonathan Bell, at <a href="mailto:student_volunteers@splashcon.org">student_volunteers@splashcon.org</a>.</p></div>\n<div class="cfp-committee-members"><h3>Student Volunteers Committee</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Gregor Richards, Purdue U, USA (chair)</li>\n<li>Jonathan Bell, Columbia U, USA (chair)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n', 1, 33, 0, 243, '2013-05-03 02:06:25', 0, '', '2013-05-03 02:06:25', 0, 0, '2013-05-03 02:06:25', '2013-05-03 02:06:25', '2033-05-03 02:06:25', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=\n', 1, 0, 1, '', '', 0, 1997, ''),
